        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 5:50PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 549 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Elizabeth, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Harrisville, North Bend State Park, Cairo, Schultz, Freeport, Walker,
Nutter Farm, Greencastle, Petroleum, and Berea.

This includes Route 50 in West Virginia between mile markers 20 and
36.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
